column5: Thats a number one report Gerritt.Nice looking fish you all caught.  Hey Goran,you told me you were a little fella.   LOL

Ever fish out from Trenton? My son is playing hockey in Trenton on the weekend and I thought I'd throw the gear in the car and head down early..... the arena is right at the lake. Any thoughts would be appreciated. Cheers!
great report gerrit, nice eyes
nice report! Thanks for sharing.
No boots and no debit card??? should have been made to sit in the truck all day!  Great report and pics!!!
WTG guys.  Nice fish.
Great stuff Gerritt! Looks BOQ was on today...  ...oh and "Boots"...go back to carrrying cash! LOL
Excellent report Gerritt!  Nice looking pickerel you lads got into there.  Corn Nug
Great report nice pics .Mike

I had cash! But I wasn't going to spend $159 on a pair of boots when I got a $150 pair at home. I was going to just run to Cdn Tire or Walmart and pickup some cheapies for the day. Big thanks to BricknBlock for the loaner boots. He saved me $40 or so on a cheapie set. If I can make it to the Tyler event, I will find a way to repay you.  Boots  Corey

You mean we were all going to Walmart...Kinda good we didnt go, we would all have had a say in your final wardrobe, it for sure would have been the Pink Barbie Boots for you brother!!! infact I woulda paid for em!! LOL    Gerritt.
Nice report guys... WTG getting the fish.. for most of ya

Great report, looks like a good time was had and some bonus fish were caught. You left at the right time i'd guess.  Went down there as well today after work. Didn't get on ice until 3:30ish stayed till 6:00 or so. No fish, some hits. The wind did get brutal, forcing me to constantly use the skimmer.  Some pics of the wind    This car was abandoned the whole time i was there.   Great report again! Nice to see some fish caught.  ehg
Great report Gerritt.  Some nice eyes there.  Goran's expression tells it all.  Joey
dude i'll make the next one, even if i have to chop the miss's into little pieces
Hey you did great!!  Congrats!!  Was hoping you folks would nail some. Way too much talent to come away empty!
looks like fun. how'd u make out scotty ?
Great report, sure sounds like a good time, wish I could have made it, maybe next time.  And I promise to remember boots
Awesome report! Good luck on the 24th!

Great!  You guys caught some nice fish, fer sure.  That looks like the flats out from Herchimer's.  Gerrit there are no pics of you.  It is easy to forget something when going fishing.  Did those boots keep his feet warm?  How many hours in total on the ice?
Beauty report, glad everyone had a good time and some fish...
Gerritt,nice report bud.You guys and girls had a great time out. With some fish to Boot LOL.  Adam,next time bring the 8inch auger,makes it a lot better to haul out them Big eyes  Steve
My feet were warm as long as I stayed moving around. When I was in my hut my toes went numb. We were on the ice from about 9:30am to 4:30pm or so... roughly 7 hours.
Just don't get much better than that.  Great report and love the pics.

Hey Clampet,   There are no pics of me because it seems I am the only one that takes pictures LOL.... besides you dont want a picture of a skunk....LOL Still trying to wash off the smell!.... I ont think anyone else took any pics... perhaps they did and hopefully they'll post em..   Gerritt.
Excellent report. Sam's folks seem to have given you a decent welcome as well. Corey, I'm afraid you're branded for life.
